parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the intake manifold can cause water intrusion, engine overheating, and other component failures, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and safety risks.
symptoms: Engine overheating
water leakage
internal cracks
and fluid on the ground.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the idle control valve can cause the engine to race, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and safety risks.
symptoms: Engine racing
sudden acceleration
and failure to stop the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission and gearbox can cause the vehicle to jump forward, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and safety risks.
symptoms: Gears popping
vehicle jumping forward
and engine oil leakage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system can cause gasoline leaks, leading to fire hazards, accidents, and safety risks.
symptoms: Strong gasoline smell
gasoline leakage
and saturated seals and tank bottoms.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of engine belts and hoses can cause the vehicle to shut down, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and safety risks.
symptoms: Belt falling off
engine coolant hose clamp coming off
and fluid leakage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Vehicle fires can cause serious safety risks, including injury and death.
symptoms: Vehicle catching fire while parked.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front ball joints can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Noise in the front passenger area
front ball joints detach from the vehicle
vehicle drops to the ground
tire blows out
and the vehicle becomes difficult to control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the suspension system can cause the vehicle to become uncontrollable, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Bouncy suspension
vehicle jumps sideways on the highway
noise in the rear passenger area
and the vehicle becomes difficult to control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear axle can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Noise in the rear passenger area
rear axle failure
and the vehicle becomes difficult to control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the coil spring can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Coil spring breaks
tire punctures
and the vehicle becomes difficult to control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of electrical components can cause the vehicle to stall or become difficult to control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Ignition key does not turn
starting relay failure
and poor connections in the lower steering column.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The absence or failure of the sway bar can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Vehicle did not have a sway bar
and the dealer claimed some vehicles do not have sway bars.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates independently
often when braking or shifting gears
with the engine racing at high RPM. The vehicle may lurch forward
and the driver may need to shift into neutral to stop the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning cruise control system can cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The cruise control fails to disengage
even when the brake pedal is applied
causing the vehicle to accelerate to high speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty throttle body or pedal can cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The accelerator pedal sticks or becomes stuck
causing the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly.
